---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const effectiveDate = "April 19, 2026";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy · Actuali" description="Privacy policy for the Actuali app.">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
    <header class="space-y-2">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">Effective {effectiveDate}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        Actuali ("the app") is a native iOS client for
        <a href="https://actualbudget.org" class="underline hover:text-neutral-900"
          >Actual Budget</a
        >, a local-first personal finance tool. This policy explains what
        information the app handles and where it goes.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        <strong>Short version:</strong> the app collects no personal data for the
        developer. Your financial data stays on your device and on the Actual Budget
        server you configure. Nothing is sent anywhere else.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Data stored on your device</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        The app stores the following on the device so it can work offline:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-neutral-700">
        <li>
          Your budget data (accounts, transactions, payees, categories, and
          monthly budgets), held in a local SQLite database.
        </li>
        <li>
          Your server URL, selected budget ID, and preferences, held in the
          system defaults store.
        </li>
        <li>
          Your authentication token for the server you configure, held in the
          iOS Keychain.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        This data never leaves your device except to synchronise with the
        Actual Budget server you specify.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Data sent over the network</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        The app communicates only with the Actual Budget server URL you enter
        in Settings. What it sends is whatever your Actual server requires:
        your login credentials, encrypted or plain sync messages, and budget
        file downloads. No other network destinations are contacted by the
        app.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        The developer of the app does not operate a server, does not see your
        traffic, and does not receive your data. If your server is
        self-hosted, your data stays entirely between you and your server.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Analytics, tracking, and ads</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        The app contains no analytics, no advertising, and no third-party
        tracking SDKs. It does not fingerprint your device or share identifiers
        with anyone.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Apple services</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        If you install the app via the App Store or TestFlight, Apple collects
        standard diagnostic information (crash logs, device model, OS version)
        subject to Apple's own privacy policy and your iOS privacy settings.
        The developer may view these aggregate reports through App Store
        Connect to fix bugs. This is Apple's system, not a third-party SDK.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Children</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        The app is not directed to children under 13 and does not knowingly
        collect information from them.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Changes</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        If this policy changes, the updated version will be posted at this URL
        with a new effective date.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        Questions about this policy or the app? Email
        <a
          href="mailto:actuali@mfazz.com"
          class="underline hover:text-neutral-900">actuali@mfazz.com</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
